n%20the%20survey%20have%20been%20dominated%20by%20tech%20giants.%20In%202017%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20most%20aspired-to%20employer%20was%20Google.%20But%20this%20year's%20rankings%2C%20based%20on%20responses%20from%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-boomers-low-employee-engagement-jobs-productivity-wfh-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Zers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reflect%20a%20changing%20world%20order.%20Google%20fell%20to%20No.%207%20on%20the%20list%3B%20Amazon%20to%20No.%208%3B%20and%20Tesla%20to%20No.%2033.%20Instagram%20came%20in%20at%20No.%2048%2C%20and%20Facebook%20just%20barely%20made%20the%20cut%20at%20all%2C%20tumbling%20all%20the%20way%20down%20past%20Dow%20Chemical%20and%203M%20to%20No.%2094.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-jobs-recession-layoffs-gen-z-students-class-of-2023-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETech's%20allure%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20appears%2C%20is%20plummeting%20among%20the%20best%20and%20brightest%20high%20schoolers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FayPKb%2F3%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Silicon%20Valley%E2%80%99s%20fading%20dominance%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22740%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20has%20tech%20suddenly%20fallen%20out%20of%20favor%20among%20students%3F%20Part%20of%20it%2C%20I'm%20guessing%2C%20is%20a%20simple%20calculation%20of%20who's%20hiring%20right%20now.%20Silicon%20Valley%20has%20been%20laying%20off%20workers%20by%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%2C%20making%20tech%20work%20almost%20impossible%20to%20come%20by.%20In%20a%20survey%20conducted%20by%20Handshake%2C%20a%20job%20site%20for%20college%20students%2C%20the%20class%20of%202024%20listed%20job%20stability%20as%20their%20top%20priority%20in%20deciding%20where%20to%20apply.%20And%20in%20the%20search%20for%20steady%20employment%2C%20the%20share%20of%20applications%20they%20submitted%20to%20tech%20companies%20dropped%20by%2019%25%20compared%20with%20the%20class%20of%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20also%20said%20a%20major%20consideration%20in%20where%20to%20apply%20was%20the%20reputation%20of%20a%20company%20as%20a%20good%20place%20to%20work.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20looking%20for%20an%20employer%20that's%20going%20to%20take%20care%20of%20them%20and%20be%20nice%20to%20their%20workforce%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Christine%20Cruzvergara%2C%20the%20chief%20education%20strategy%20officer%20at%20Handshake.%20And%20the%20tech%20industry%20did%20itself%20no%20favors%20in%20the%20harsh%20way%20it%20conducted%20its%20recent%20wave%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-firings-tech-hr-tiktok-cloudflare-employee-morale-bad-business-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20seen%20people%20go%20on%20social%20media%20and%20talk%20about%20what%20their%20layoff%20experience%20was%20like%20and%20how%20the%20company%20treated%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Cruzvergara%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20numbers%20suggest%20that%20tech's%20disfavor%20among%20Gen%20Z%20is%20more%20than%20self-interested%20calculus.%20For%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20tech%20has%20enjoyed%20a%20near-total%20monopoly%20on%20the%20country's%20smartest%20young%20workers.%20Millennials%20believed%20they%20were%20heading%20to%20Silicon%20Valley%20in%20service%20of%20a%20lofty%20mission.%20Tech%2C%20they%20were%20told%2C%20was%20going%20to%20democratize%20data%2C%20creating%20a%20digital%20bridge%20to%20a%20better%20and%20more%20equitable%20world.%20Instead%2C%20tech%20companies%20have%20been%20responsible%20for%20spreading%20misinformation%2C%20fueling%20hate%20speech%2C%20sowing%20digital%20addiction%2C%20and%20exacerbating%20an%20epidemic%20of%20mental%20illness%20among%20teens.%20To%20Gen%20Z%2C%20tech%20no%20longer%20looks%20like%20a%20force%20for%20good.%20On%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nshss.org%2Fmedia%2Fl3slxj5k%2Fnshss-2024-career-and-interests-survey.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-school%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year%2C%20more%20students%20said%20they%20believe%20artificial%20intelligence%20will%20have%20a%20negative%20effect%20on%20society%20than%20those%20who%20say%20it%20will%20have%20a%20positive%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20seen%20this%20happen%20before.%20Two%20decades%20ago%2C%20when%20I%20was%20in%20college%2C%20the%20smartest%20students%20in%20my%20class%20wanted%20to%20go%20into%20finance.%20Then%2C%20in%20the%20fall%20semester%20of%20our%20senior%20year%2C%20Lehman%20Brothers%20collapsed%20and%20took%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20economy%20with%20it.%20The%20sharp%20contraction%20in%20banking%20%E2%80%94%20combined%20with%20Wall%20Street's%20new%20image%20as%20evil%20personified%20%E2%80%94%20spurred%20students%20to%20begin%20looking%20elsewhere%20for%20employment.%20That's%20when%20the%20Googles%20and%20Facebooks%20swooped%20in%2C%20offering%20wildly%20generous%20stock%20options%2C%20free%20meals%2C%20offices%20with%20ping-pong%20tables%2C%20and%20a%20chance%20to%20build%20world-changing%20products.%20It%20didn't%20take%20long%20for%20tech%20to%20supplant%20finance%20as%20the%20ultimate%20dream%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20waning%20interest%20in%20Big%20Tech%20could%20pose%20a%20long-term%20threat%20to%20its%20future.%20After%20all%2C%20the%20industry's%20ascent%20was%20fueled%20by%20more%20than%20its%20algorithms.%20Part%20of%20what%20made%20Silicon%20Valley%20so%20dominant%20was%20the%20endless%20pipeline%20of%20brilliant%20college%20graduates%20who%20supplied%20young%20companies%20with%20the%20fresh%20ideas%20and%20mountains%20of%20code%20they%20needed%20to%20become%20the%20behemoths%20they%20are%20today.%20If%20Big%20Tech%20has%20lost%20the%20hearts%20and%20minds%20of%20today's%20students%2C%20it%20has%20lost%20its%20ultimate%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Silicon%20Valley%20is%20going%20out%20of%20vogue%2C%20what%20will%20take%20its%20place%20as%20the%20next%20hot%20destination%3F%20One%20contender%2C%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20high-school%20survey%2C%20appears%20to%20be%20healthcare.%20In%20this%20year's%20rankings%2C%20St.%20Jude%20Children's%20Research%20Hospital%20was%20No.%201.%20The%20Mayo%20Clinic%20was%20No.%202.%20The%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%2C%20which%20wasn't%20even%20in%20the%20top%20100%20in%202018%2C%20was%20No.%2014.%20If%20the%20pandemic%20taught%20Gen%20Z%20anything%2C%20it's%20that%20no%20jobs%20are%20more%20important%20than%20those%20of%20the%20front-line%20workers%20who%20put%20their%20own%20lives%20on%20the%20line%20to%20save%20the%20lives%20of%20others.%20(Students%20ranked%20their%20local%20hospital%20at%20No.%204.)%20And%20with%20the%20healthcare%20industry%20facing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-hospital-wait-times-are-bad-physician-shortage-low-pay-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esevere%20staffing%20shortages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20need%20young%20people%20to%20pursue%20careers%20as%20doctors%20and%20nurses%20far%20more%20than%20we%20need%20them%20to%20optimize%20ads%20on%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FxOmrd%2F3%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20next%20hot%20jobs%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22909%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20contender%20to%20take%20tech's%20place%20may%20be%20%E2%80%94%20irony%20of%20ironies%20%E2%80%94%20the%20federal%20government.%20Civil%20service%20doesn't%20come%20with%20the%20pay%20or%20the%20glamour%20of%20tech%20jobs%2C%20but%20it%20offers%20the%20stability%20that%20college%20students%20say%20they%20want.%20Perhaps%20that's%20why%20the%20share%20of%20applications%20to%20government%20jobs%20on%20Handshake%20this%20year%20nearly%20doubled%20from%202022.%20And%20in%20the%20survey%20of%20high%20schoolers%2C%20the%20FBI%2C%20NASA%2C%20the%20CIA%2C%20and%20the%20CDC%20all%20ranked%20in%20the%20top%2020.%20Big%20Tech's%20biggest%20titans%20may%20loathe%20Washington%2C%20but%20today's%20smartest%20teenagers%20see%20it%20as%20a%20source%20of%20meaningful%20work%20and%20steady%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20I've%20chewed%20this%20question%20over%2C%20I%20wonder%20if%20the%20new%20dream%20job%20for%20young%20people%20isn't%20a%20job%20at%20all%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20not%20the%20kind%20where%20they%20work%20for%20someone%20else.%20On%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjoinhandshake.com%2Fdocs%2Fnetwork-trends%2Fclass-of-2024-graduation.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHandshake%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20three-quarters%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20would%20be%20interested%20in%20pursuing%20entrepreneurship%20at%20some%20point%20in%20their%20career.%20Many%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20have%20already%20dabbled%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20side%20hustles%2C%20acquiring%20a%20taste%20for%20working%20for%20themselves.%20When%20I%20speak%20to%20college%20students%20these%20days%2C%20I'm%20struck%20by%20how%20they%20lack%20the%20naivete%20I%20suffered%20from%20when%20I%20was%20their%20age.%20They%20already%20know%20that%20the%20only%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyou%20can't%20get%20fired%20from%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20one%20where%20you're%20the%20owner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20they%20plan%20on%20striking%20out%20on%20their%20own%20right%20away.%20That%20would%20be%20the%20opposite%20of%20the%20stability%20they%20want%2C%20and%20this%20is%20a%20practical%20bunch.%20Instead%2C%20they're%20still%20applying%20for%20normal%2C%20entry-level%20jobs%20to%20support%20themselves%20while%20they%20spin%20up%20their%20own%20thing.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20using%20their%20full-time%20job%20as%20a%20safety%20net%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20they%20have%20steady%20income%2C%20that%20they're%20able%20to%20pay%20their%20bills%2C%20that%20they're%20able%20to%20save%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Cruzvergara.%20%26quot%3BThen%2C%20if%20things%20are%20going%20well%2C%20they%20can%20make%20that%20transition%20and%20it%20doesn't%20feel%20as%20idealistic%20and%20scary.%26quot%3B%20Today's%20students%20may%20not%20%3Cem%3Elook%3C%2Fem%3E%20all%20that%20different%20from%20the%20careerists%20of%20previous%20generations.%20But%20their%20North%20Star%20is%20no%20longer%20to%20become%20a%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20someone%20else's%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20ends%20up%20becoming%20the%20next%20hot%20career%20%E2%80%94%20healthcare%2C%20government%2C%20entrepreneurship%2C%20or%20something%20else%20%E2%80%94%20the%20waning%20dominance%20of%20Big%20Tech%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20a%20good%20thing%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20economy.%20So%20many%20sectors%20have%20languished%20for%20years%2C%20unable%20to%20compete%20for%20the%20bright%20young%20minds%20that%20Silicon%20Valley%20hoarded%20for%20so%20long.%20Now%2C%20like%20tech%20and%20finance%20before%20them%2C%20they'll%20finally%20have%20a%20shot%20at%20hiring%20the%20generation%20that%20will%20drive%20the%20innovation%20of%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-hot-jobs-tech-layoffs-healthcare-government-careers-202