ter%20graduating%2C%20keeping%20two%20jobs%20was%20a%20no-brainer.%20She%20landed%20a%209-to-5%20as%20a%20marketing%20specialist%20and%20kept%20her%20service%20job.%20In%20the%20first%20half%20of%202024%2C%20she%20earned%20%2443%2C000%20in%20Canadian%20dollars%20and%20saved%20up%2070%25%20of%20her%20salary.%20All%20the%20while%2C%20she%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-living-home-challenging-societal-norms-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliving%20at%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20renting%20out%20her%20college%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20she%20was%20getting%20closer%20to%20her%20goal%20of%20early%20retirement%2C%20she%20struggled%20to%20find%20the%20time%20or%20energy%20to%20maintain%20her%20hobbies%2C%20social%20life%2C%20or%20sleep%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3EWhen%20the%20sun%20goes%20down%20at%206%20p.m.%20in%20winter%2C%20I've%20had%20days%20where%20I%20look%20out%20of%20the%20window%20and%20realize%20I've%20had%20no%20sun%20or%20exercise%20all%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Jane%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20reduced%20her%20customer%20service%20job%20by%2010%20hours%20a%20week%20to%20alleviate%20exhaustion%20but%20still%20felt%20burned%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20it's%20not%20good%20for%20my%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%20or%20my%20sleep%2C%20but%20I'm%20so%20focused%20on%20my%20goal%20that%20I'm%20willing%20to%20sacrifice%20that%20for%20a%20few%20more%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ec8f53f5-c9ef-4a0f-8606-2b7d53e8470c%5C%22%3EThis%20project%20manager%20took%20jobs%20on%20each%20coast%20to%20work%2012-hour%20days%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20project%20management%20job%20went%20remote%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%2030-year-old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fover-employed-double-dip-how-to-work-multiple-jobs-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKendall%20McGill%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20BI%20she%20used%20the%20time%20at%20home%20to%20start%20a%20contract%20job%20with%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20when%20her%20manager%20found%20out%20about%20the%20job%20and%20confronted%20her%20with%20concerns%2C%20McGill%20said%20she%20knew%20she%20had%20to%20be%20more%20secretive%20if%20she%20wanted%20to%20keep%20double-dipping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202022%2C%20she%20left%20her%20full-time%20job%20and%20created%20a%20job-juggling%20system%20to%20avoid%20legal%20and%20professional%20consequences.%20However%2C%20it%20required%20major%20upkeep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcGill%20told%20BI%20that%20she%20steered%20clear%20of%20jobs%20with%20mandatory%20hours%2C%20in-person%20meetings%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicromanager-boss-being-better-manager-tips-advice-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicromanagement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20even%20took%20jobs%20on%20opposite%20coasts%20to%20work%2012-hour%20days%20without%20crossover.%20The%20most%20extreme%20tactic%20was%20her%20interview%20technique.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20multiple%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20highlighting%20different%20skills%20and%20jobs%20rather%20than%20listing%20all%20my%20jobs%20simultaneously.%20If%20it%20ever%20does%20come%20up%2C%20I%20make%20it%20seem%20like%20the%20dates%20overlap%20less%20than%20they%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20McGill%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20time%20that%20an%20interviewer%20asked%20about%20overlap%2C%20she%20didn't%20get%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20risky%20overlaps%20and%20long%20hours%2C%20McGill%20said%20she%20was%20happy%20with%20her%20choice.%20She%20was%20able%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20using%20four%20months%20of%20savings%20and%20felt%20motivated%20to%20keep%20working%20multiple%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20sold%20this%20American%20dream%2C%20but%20how%20can%20you%20achieve%20it%20with%20inflation%2C%20a%20pandemic%2C%20layoffs%2C%20and%20all%20these%20other%20things%3F%20The%20on