c.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2F11ldsc4o_budget_625x300_16_July_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20budgets%20that%20follow%20the%20interim%20budgets%20announced%20by%20the%20same%20government%20do%20not%20have%20many%20changes.%20There%20is%20no%20reason%20to%20expect%20differences%20this%20time%2C%20considering%20the%20economy%20is%20performing%20well%20and%20growing%20at%20above%207%25%20for%20FY25%2C%20with%20all%20high-frequency%20indicators%20being%20positive.%20So%2C%20what%20should%20we%20look%20for%20in%20the%20budget%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20a%20tendency%20to%20outline%20the%20economic%20ideology%20in%20every%20budget%2C%20with%20the%20Finance%20Minister%20highlighting%20the%20areas%20of%20focus.%20Education%20and%20skill%20development%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20emphasised%2C%20as%20they%20are%20medium-term%20goals%20of%20the%20government%20to%20ensure%20sustainable%20employment%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Fiscal%20Deficit%20Ratio%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20content%2C%20the%20following%20issues%20are%20of%20interest.%20First%20is%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20ratio%20targeted%20for%20the%20year.%20The%20interim%20budget%20mentioned%205.1%25%2C%20which%20worked%20out%20to%205.2%25%20when%20the%20provisional%20numbers%20for%20nominal%20GDP%20came%20in%20lower.%20Since%20all%20budgets%20are%20drafted%20after%20pegging%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20ratio%2C%20this%20will%20be%20the%20starting%20point.%20It%20may%20be%20expected%20that%20a%20slightly%20lower%20number%2C%20around%205%25%2C%20will%20be%20targeted%20to%20make%20the%20task%20for%20FY26%20more%20manageable%2C%20which%20is%20aiming%20for%20a%204.5%25%20deficit.%20There%20might%20also%20be%20indications%20for%20the%20future%20fiscal%20path%2C%20as%20with%20steady%20economic%20growth%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20the%20goal%20of%203%25%20could%20be%20back%20on%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20market%20is%20abuzz%20with%20the%20deployment%20of%20the%20additional%20Rs%201%20lakh%20crore%20that%20the%20RBI%20has%20passed%20on%20to%20the%20government.%20For%20the%20entire%20banking%20sector%2C%20the%20target%20was%20Rs%201.1%20lakh%20crore%2C%20which%20included%20dividends%20paid%20by%20the%20PSBs%20and%20other%20public%20financial%20institutions.%20As%20the%20surplus%20to%20be%20transferred%20is%20at%20least%20Rs%201%20lakh%20crore%20higher%2C%20there%20is%20a%20cushion%20provided%20to%20the%20RBI.%20At%20one%20extreme%2C%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20could%20be%20reduced%20from%20Rs%2016.85%20lakh%20crore%20to%20Rs%2015.85%20lakh%20crore.%20More%20likely%2C%20this%20advantage%20will%20be%20partly%20used%20to%20address%20other%20issues%20in%20the%20budget%20on%20both%20the%20expenditure%20and%20revenue%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETax%20Rationalisation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20on%20the%20revenue%20side%2C%20there%20is%20a%20call%20for%20tax%20rationalisation%2C%20especially%20at%20the%20individual%20level.%20Consumption%20has%20been%20tepid%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%20due%20to%20lower%20income%20generation%20at%20the%20household%20level%20and%20high%20cumulative%20inflation%2C%20reducing%20individuals'%20purchasing%20power.%20Cutting%20tax%20rates%20or%20widening%20the%20income%20slabs%20for%20taxation%20will%20help%20stimulate%20consumption.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20salaried%20class%2C%20which%20pays%20the%20highest%20taxes%20to%20the%20government%2C%20including%20GST%2C%20has%20not%20received%20any%20benefits%20so%20far.%20And%20they%20are%20looking%20at%20the%20budget%20with%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFourth%2C%20savings%20have%20been%20affected%20in%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20with%20household%20financial%20savings%20declining.%20This%20trend%20followed%20the%20pent-up%20demand%20phenomenon%20and%20higher%20inflation%2C%20which%20shifted%20income%20towards%20essential%20consumption.%20To%20revive%20savings%2C%20the%20government%20could%20encourage%20savings%20through%20tax-saving%20schemes%20and%20interest%20paid%20on%20home%20loans.%20This%20would%20help%20increase%20both%20income%20and%20savings.%20This%20measure%2C%20along%20with%20tax%20cuts%2C%20will%20address%20issues%20of%20consumption%20and%20savings.%20The%20old%20tax%20scheme%20can%20be%20reviewed%20from%20the%20savings%20perspective%2C%20while%20the%20new%20tax%20scheme%20can%20promote%20increased%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFifth%2C%20investment%20has%20been%20slow%20to%20pick%20up%20due%20to%20limited%20private%20investment%2C%20caused%20by%20surplus%20capacity.%20To%20break%20this%20gridlock%2C%20demand%20needs%20to%20be%20generated%2C%20which%20can%20happen%20only%20with%20increased%20income%2C%20dependent%20on%20job%20creation.%20From%20a%20fiscal%20standpoint%2C%20focusing%20on%20MSMEs%20could%20be%20a%20solution%2C%20as%20they%20contribute%20to%20job%20creation%2C%20exports%2C%20and%20industrial%20growth.%20A%20PLI%20scheme%20for%20this%20segment%20would%20help%20achieve%20these%20objectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20Increasing%20Capex%20And%20Decreasing%20Borrowing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESixth%2C%20as%20private%20sector%20investment%20is%20still%20narrow%20and%20not%20broad-based%2C%20there%20is%20a%20strong%20case%20for%20the%20government%20to%20continue%20increasing%20capex.%20The%20government%20has%20the%20option%20to%20increase%20the%20outlay%20from%20the%20current%20level%20of%20Rs%2011.11%20lakh%20crore%2C%20given%20the%20surplus%20received%20from%20the%20RBI.%20However%2C%20there%20may%20be%20limited%20capacity%20in%20terms%20of%20available%20projects%20in%20roads%20and%20railways%3B%20so%20the%20increase%20would%20be%20marginal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeventh%2C%20with%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20being%20lowered%2C%20the%20government's%20overall%20borrowing%20could%2