tthew%20Crooks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%2020-year-old%20shooter%20from%20Bethel%20Park%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20for%20a%20police%20sniper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20said%20that%20Crooks%20fired%20multiple%20rounds%20from%20a%20rooftop%20around%20150%20meters%20away%20from%20Trump%20using%20an%20AR-15%20rifle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20a%20Secret%20Service%20sniper%20must%20have%20had%20a%20clear%20view%20of%20the%20rooftop%20because%20the%20gunman%2C%20Thomas%20Matthew%20Crooks%2C%20was%20shot%20dead%20within%20a%20few%20seconds%20of%20opening%20fire%20on%20Trump%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Figliuzzi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20why%20did%20that%20sniper%20ignore%20Crooks%20till%20then%3F%20One%20plausible%20explanation%20is%20that%20the%20Secret%20Service%20(which%20is%20entirely%20separate%20from%20the%20FBI)%20assumed%20the%20assassin%20was%20a%20police%20sniper%2C%20part%20of%20their%20security%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20Figliuzzi%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20wrote%20that%20such%20a%20case%20%26quot%3Bimplies%20serious%20failures%20in%20communication.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20expect%20police%20and%20Secret%20Service%20teams%20to%20not%20only%20meet%20and%20introduce%20themselves%20but%20map%20out%20their%20specific%20roles%20in%20detail%2C%26quot%3B%20Figliuzzi%20said%20in%20his%20opinion%20piece.%20%26quot%3BThey%20ought%20to%20have%20been%20able%20to%20recognize%20each%20other%20by%20sight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFigliuzzi%20also%20wrote%20that%20he%20disagreed%20with%20what%20the%20Secret%20Service%20agents%20did%20during%20the%20rally%2C%20like%20letting%20Trump%20pause%20to%20pose%20for%20a%20photo%20with%20his%20face%20bloodied%20or%20complying%20with%20his%20request%20to%20retrieve%20his%20shoes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20that%20moment%2C%20the%20Secret%20Service%20had%20no%20way%20of%20knowing%20if%20the%20gunman%20was%20acting%20alone.%20Other%20shooters%20might%20have%20been%20present%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote